    {
      "type": "block-update-html",
      "pageId": "d7e53ed0-638d-4df8-943d-b5513d367558",
      "blockId": "1b0921bb-7eba-4d1c-b726-3296f234cfc9",
      "html": "<ul><li>DNA</li></ul><ul><li>DNA synthesis</li><li>DNA manipulation</li><li>DNA replication</li><li>Restriction enzymes</li><li>RNA</li><ul><li>mRNA</li><ul><li>codons</li></ul><li>tRNA</li><ul><li>anti codon</li></ul></ul><li>Central Dogma</li><ul><li>DNA -&gt; mRNA -&gt; Amino acid chain (polypeptide) -&gt; Folding into 3D protein</li></ul><li>Transcription</li><li>Translation</li><li>Eukaryotic</li><li>Prokaryotic</li><li>Protein synthesis</li><li>Plasmids</li><li>Peptide synthesis</li><li>Pippetting&nbsp;</li><ul><li>Units</li><ul><li>Moles - absolute amount of substance</li><li><span style=\"caret-color: var(--text); color: var(--text); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, sans-serif;\">Molarity - concentration</span></li></ul><li>Assays</li><li>Serial dilutions</li></ul></ul><p><br></p>",
      "deviceId": "85e62a38-d748-4481-9925-9591e05e321f",
      "timestamp": 1772284884605,
      "id": "fe7cf955-5982-4401-9770-310abe2295a6"
    },
    {
      "type": "block-update-html",
      "pageId": "d7e53ed0-638d-4df8-943d-b5513d367558",
      "blockId": "9fa0a121-aab4-4618-8bca-76b245305c69",
      "html": "<b>Recombinant expression</b><div>1. Clone the coding sequence into an expression vector (a plasmid).</div><div>2. Transform the plasmid into host cells.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1. Bacteria are given a heat shock.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2. Colonies grow.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3. Pick colonies.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4. Inoculate the liquid cultures (by introducing single colonies)</div><div>3. Transcription + Translation</div><div>4. Harvest. Cells are lysed. Protein is purified.</div>",
